 {"id":"bd-2kr1","title":"[ALIEN][RAPTORQ] Systematic encoding (precode + LT) deterministic","description":"## Purpose

Implement an RFC-class systematic encoder:
- produce K source symbols (systematic part)
- then produce repair symbols based on robust soliton + precode

## Determinism requirements

- Degree selection and neighbor selection must be seeded from explicit DetRng.
- Encoding must not depend on iteration order of HashMaps etc.

## Acceptance criteria

- For fixed seed + input, emitted symbols are identical across runs.
- Repair symbols match the spec's distribution and construction.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-03T00:12:45.969839970Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-03T04:21:42.422482761Z","closed_at":"2026-02-03T04:21:42.422321261Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["alien","encoding","raptorq"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2kr1","depends_on_id":"bd-201j","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:30:28Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-2kr1","depends_on_id":"bd-39fr","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:30:28Z","created_by":"import"}]}
 {"id":"bd-2ktrc","title":"[TESTING] Comprehensive Testing & Fault Injection Suite","description":"Build Asupersync's testing infrastructure to Gold/Platinum quality (§0.14). Mandatory fault suite (from plan): message reorder/duplication, partition, crash/restart, clock skew. Pass criteria: liveness preserved + no obligation leak + deterministic replay parity. This includes: (1) Property-based tests with shrinking for all core protocols, (2) Deterministic replay tests using Lab runtime, (3) Fault injection scenarios for all failure modes, (4) Conformance tests against tokio test suite (compatibility target), (5) Loom-based concurrency testing for lock-free primitives (Tier C assurance). Each test must log extensively with structured JSON for debugging.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-13T09:19:25.895639539Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T09:23:18.738740456Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["fault-injection","quality","testing"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2ktrc","depends_on_id":"bd-1e2if","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:30:28Z","created_by":"import"}]}
-{"id":"bd-2ktrc.1","title":"[TESTING] Implement fault injection for message reorder/duplication","description":"Implement fault injection hooks that simulate message reorder and duplication in Asupersync's channel system. This tests that obligation protocols remain correct when messages arrive out of order or are duplicated. Implementation: (1) Add a FaultInjector trait with reorder_probability and duplication_probability parameters, (2) Hook into the channel send path to intercept messages and apply faults, (3) Reorder: buffer N messages and emit in random permutation, (4) Duplication: clone message and deliver twice. Lab runtime integration: faults are deterministic (seeded PRNG) and replayable. Pass criteria: (a) No obligation leak under any fault scenario, (b) Idempotency — duplicated messages do not cause double-processing, (c) Eventual delivery — reordered messages are all eventually delivered. Must log all injected faults to EvidenceLedger for debugging.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T09:19:36.121232506Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T20:47:12.793858551Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["fault-injection","messages","testing"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2ktrc.1","depends_on_id":"bd-1e2if.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:30:30Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-2ktrc.1","depends_on_id":"bd-2ktrc","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:30:30Z","created_by":"import"}]}
-{"id":"bd-2ktrc.2","title":"[TESTING] Implement fault injection for network partition","description":"Implement fault injection for simulating network partitions between Asupersync actors and services. Partitions are the most critical fault type — they test whether the saga system correctly detects unreachable participants and triggers compensation. Implementation: (1) Partition model: define which actor pairs can communicate (connectivity graph), (2) Partition injection: block message delivery between partitioned actors, (3) Partition healing: restore connectivity after configurable duration, (4) Partial partition: asymmetric partitions where A can reach B but not vice versa. Lab runtime integration: partitions are scheduled events in virtual time. Pass criteria: (a) Saga compensation triggers correctly under partition, (b) No split-brain — partitioned actors do not make conflicting decisions, (c) Recovery after partition heal — system converges to consistent state, (d) Budget/deadline expiry during partition causes correct cancellation. Must test: 2-way, 3-way, and cascading partitions.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T09:19:45.081462050Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T09:23:28.505523004Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["fault-injection","partition","testing"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2ktrc.2","depends_on_id":"bd-1e2if.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:30:30Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-2ktrc.2","depends_on_id":"bd-2ktrc","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:30:30Z","created_by":"import"}]}
-{"id":"bd-2ktrc.3","title":"[TESTING] Implement fault injection for crash/restart","description":"Implement fault injection for simulating actor crash and restart in Asupersync. Crash faults test whether the supervision tree correctly detects failed actors, cleans up their obligations, and restarts them. Implementation: (1) Crash injection: kill actor at random point during execution (after N operations or at specific protocol step), (2) Restart model: restart actor with fresh state (cold restart) or from last checkpoint (warm restart), (3) Cascade crash: crash supervisor to test supervision tree recovery. Lab runtime integration: crashes are scheduled events with deterministic timing. Pass criteria: (a) All obligations held by crashed actor are released (no leak), (b) Supervisor detects crash and restarts within configured timeout, (c) Restarted actor resumes from correct protocol state, (d) In-flight messages to crashed actor are properly handled (timeout or redirect), (e) Crash during two-phase commit triggers abort, not partial commit. Must test: single crash, double crash, supervisor crash, crash during cancellation.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T09:19:52.775914435Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T09:23:29.672107867Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crash","fault-injection","testing"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2ktrc.3","depends_on_id":"bd-1e2if.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:30:23Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-2ktrc.3","depends_on_id":"bd-2ktrc","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:30:23Z","created_by":"import"}]}
